WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:41.115
Welcome to Grade 8 English, Unit 7: Historical Figures and Legacy. Welcome to Unit 7 of your Year 8 English course. In this unit, you will explore the theme of Historical Figures and Legacy - a topic that invites you to think about how individuals shape history and how their actions echo through generations. You will read a powerful story set in 1948 East Africa, learn essential grammar structures for narrating past events, and build a rich vocabulary for discussing argument, leadership, emotion, and change. In this short lecture, preview the key ideas and prepare for the independent lesson.

2
00:00:41.195 --> 00:01:12.740
By the end of this unit, you will be able to use the past simple and past continuous tenses correctly to narrate events and describe actions in progress in the past. you will also form and use the past perfect tense to show which action happened first when telling a story. you will also convert direct speech into reported speech, adjusting pronouns, verb tenses, and word order correctly. Keep these goals in mind as you work.

3
00:01:12.820 --> 00:01:30.632
Your vocabulary work begins with these words: 1. benign, 2. reprieve, 3. defect, 4. disposition, 5. systematic, 6. cache. Listen to each pronunciation in the vocabulary lab, study its meaning in context, and use the word accurately in your own discussion and writing.

4
00:01:30.712 --> 00:01:47.277
The reading sequence includes Historical Figures and Legacy: source text 1 and Historical Figures and Legacy: source text 2. Read actively. Identify each text's central ideas, notice viewpoint and reliability, and support every inference with relevant evidence from the text.

5
00:01:47.357 --> 00:02:04.753
The first language focus is How to Form Them. Past Simple - Regular Verbs: Add -ed to the base form of the verb. play -> played Notice the structure in the model examples, then apply it deliberately in connected sentences and paragraphs.

6
00:02:04.833 --> 00:02:19.733
In speaking, you will complete Speaking 1: Story Retelling. Organise your ideas, use evidence and respond clearly to questions. In writing, you will plan, draft, check and revise. Use the success criteria before submitting your work.

7
00:02:19.813 --> 00:02:36.794
You are ready to begin. Start with the vocabulary lab, continue through reading and comprehension, apply the grammar focus, and complete the speaking and writing practices. Use AI English for hints and feedback, and bring your questions to the live sessions.
